<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="787" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11285a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-24T17:00:00-05:00">November 24, 1937—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>314. The <hi rend="italic">New York Herald Tribune</hi> today carries
                                an article by Fleisher, under Tokyo date line November 23, the first
                                sentence of which reads as follows: “That Japan’s political idea is
                                to establish a United States of Asia is the argument advanced in a
                                pamphlet being distributed to foreign correspondents ‘with the
                                compliments’ of Premier Prince Fumimaro Konoye.”</p>
                            <p>Please endeavor to obtain a copy of the pamphlet and forward it to
                                Department by pouch with the Embassy’s comment thereon.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>